The African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA) aims at integrating African markets to address challenges emanating from the continent’s reliance on world markets. The AfCFTA has the potential to help African economies create more value in local and regional markets which in turn will help reduce vulnerabilities. Enhanced continental integration through the implementation of the Agreement will enable the economies of scale and investment necessary to develop regional value chains and support the continent’s transformational industrialization. 



